Category 2: Compute & Networking (EC2, VPC, ELB)
How do you choose between a Network Load Balancer (NLB) and an Application Load Balancer (ALB)? (p. 2)

ANSWER
------
        🚦 ALB vs NLB – How to Choose?
        🧠 Interview-Ready Answer

        👉 “I choose between Application Load Balancer (ALB) and Network Load Balancer (NLB) based on the application layer and requirements.”

        If I need content-based routing, HTTP/HTTPS, microservices → I use ALB
        If I need ultra-high performance, low latency, TCP/UDP → I use NLB
        | Feature     | ALB                    | NLB                    |
        | ----------- | ---------------------- | ---------------------- |
        | Layer       | Layer 7 (Application)  | Layer 4 (Transport)    |
        | Protocols   | HTTP, HTTPS            | TCP, UDP               |
        | Routing     | Path-based, host-based | IP + Port only         |
        | Performance | Moderate               | Very high              |
        | Latency     | Slightly higher        | Ultra-low              |
        | Use Case    | Web apps, APIs         | Real-time apps, gaming |



