What is the difference between a Security Group and a Network ACL (NACL)? (p. 1)
ANSWER
------
    Security Groups and Network ACLs both control traffic in AWS, but the key difference is that Security Groups are stateful and instance-level, while NACLs are stateless and subnet-level


